_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/538020?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc","html_url":"https://github.com/ferdnyc","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-09-11T06:29:48Z","updated_at":"2025-09-11T06:30:47Z","body":"Looks like the issue is that argparse's default formatter uses `textwrap.fill()` to format the output, and `textwrap.fill()` will break URLs by default:\n\n```python\n>>> description=(\"Adjust how values of type 'None' are handled. For more context on \"\n... + \"how mypy handles values of type 'None', see: \"\n... + \"https://mypy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/kinds_of_types.html#optional-types-and-the-none-type\")\n>>> print(textwrap.fill(description))\nAdjust how values of type 'None' are handled. For more context on how\nmypy handles values of type 'None', see:\nhttps://mypy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/kinds_of_types.html#optional-\ntypes-and-the-none-type\n```\n\nBut it can be convinced to operate differently:\n\n```python\n>>> print(textwrap.fill(description, break_on_hyphens=False))\nAdjust how values of type 'None' are handled. For more context on how\nmypy handles values of type 'None', see: https://mypy.readthedocs.io/e\nn/stable/kinds_of_types.html#optional-types-and-the-none-type\n>>> print(textwrap.fill(description, break_on_hyphens=False, break_long_words=False))\nAdjust how values of type 'None' are handled. For more context on how\nmypy handles values of type 'None', see:\nhttps://mypy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/kinds_of_types.html#optional-types-and-the-none-type\n```\n\nSo, maybe a subclass of [`HelpFormatter`](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/afec6a546049b80fdbaf18baa3a4d2cbc535ce58/Lib/argparse.py#L155) that overrides `_fill_text()`?\n\n```python\n# Instead of this\n    def _fill_text(self, text, width, indent):\n        text = self._whitespace_matcher.sub(' ', text).strip()\n        import textwrap\n        return textwrap.fill(text, width,\n                             initial_indent=indent,\n                             subsequent_indent=indent)\n# Do this\n    def _fill_text(self, text, width, indent):\n        text = self._whitespace_matcher.sub(' ', text).strip()\n        import textwrap\n        return textwrap.fill(text, width,\n                             initial_indent=indent,\n                             subsequent_indent=indent,\n                             break_on_hyphens=False,\n                             break_long_words=False)\n```\n\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/python/mypy/issues/comments/3278402942/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"ferdnyc","id":538020,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzODAyMA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/538020?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc","html_url":"https://github.com/ferdnyc","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ferdnyc/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fer